It is important to convey at the outset that Article 8 plays a limited role in the securities markets. Article 8 does not govern contracts for the purchase and sale of securities, cle- aring arrangements, or regulate the relationships between and among cleäring corporations, brbkers, or dealers, and their customers except to the extent such entities act as se- curities intermediaries. Article 8 and Article 9 simply provi- de the rules for identifying the rights, interests, obligations and priorities of interests in securities, whether certificated or uncertificated, held directly or through intermediaries. As noted above, many important issues regarding the securities markets in the United States are governed by State and Fe- deral securities laws and regulations and State and Federal

the UCC.
